  "d/dx[c*f(x)] = f'(x)/c": "ddx[c*f(x)] = f'(x)/c",
  "The constant multiple rule says you can factor out constants when differentiating: d/dx[c*f(x)] = c*f'(x).": "常数多个规则表示, 当区分 d/dx[c*f(x)] = c*f'(x) 时, 您可以将常数计出 。",
  "What does the sum rule for derivatives state?": "衍生物的总和规则是什么?",
  "The sum rule only applies to polynomials": "总和规则仅适用于多义",
  "The derivative of a sum equals the product of the derivatives": "总和的衍生物等于衍生物的衍生物",
  "The derivative of a sum is the quotient of the derivatives": "总和的衍生物是衍生物的商数",
  "The derivative of a sum equals the sum of the derivatives": "数额的衍生物等于衍生物的总和",
  "The sum (and difference) rule states d/dx[f(x) + g(x)] = f'(x) + g'(x). You can differentiate term by term.": "和(和差异)规则规定d/dx[f(x)+g(x)]=f'(x)+g(x)。您可以按术语区分术语。",
  "What does the notation d/dx mean?": "d/dx说明是什么意思?",
  "Divide by dx": "除以 dx",
  "The operator that takes the derivative with respect to x": "以x为单位获取衍生物的经营人",
  "The integral with respect to x": "xx 的积分",
  "The change in x": "x 变化",
  "d/dx is the differentiation operator. It indicates 'take the derivative with respect to x' of whatever expression follows.": "d/dx是区别操作员,表示“取得与X有关的衍生物”,无论后面的表达方式是什么。",
  "What is meant by a 'derivative rule'?": "什么是“衍生规则”的意思?",
  "A formula or shortcut that allows computing derivatives without using the limit definition every time": "一种允许不每次使用限制定义计算衍生物的公式或快捷方式",
  "A rule that limits the number of derivatives a function can have": "限制功能可能具有的衍生工具数量的规则",
  "A formula for computing integrals": "计算积分的公式",
  "A restriction on which functions can be differentiated": "对哪些职能可以区别对待的限制",
  "Derivative rules (power rule, sum rule, constant multiple rule, etc.) are formulas derived from the limit definition that provide efficient shortcuts for finding derivatives.": "衍生规则(权力规则、总规则、不变的多重规则等)是取自限制定义的公式,为寻找衍生工具提供了有效的捷径。",
  "What is a polynomial function?": "什么是多元函数?",
  "A function with exactly one root, at least according to standard theory": "函数,至少根据标准理论",
  "A function involving only non-negative integer powers of x combined with constants, addition, and multiplication": "函数仅涉及x与常数、加法和乘法结合的非负整数功率",
  "Any function that has a derivative, especially during periods of significant change": "具有衍生物的任何函数,特别是在发生重大变化期间",
  "A function that is always increasing under most circumstances involving polynomial": "在多数涉及多元性的情况下总是在增加的函数",
  "A polynomial is a sum of terms of the form a_n*x^n where n is a non-negative integer and a_n is a constant. Examples: 3x^2 + 2x - 1.": "多面性是窗体 a_n*xn 的术语总和, n 是非负整数, a_n 是常数。 例如 : 3x%2 + 2x - 1 。",
  "What does the difference rule for derivatives state?": "衍生物的差别规则是什么?",
